title: Temporary fix of the bugged fetch magnet mechanism
message:
Temporary fix of the bugged fetch magnet mechanism

This commit is a workaround for problems with the incorrect behavior of some trackers and the inability to change the priority of files (issues #93, #111) that are contained in the jlibtorrent library because the developers at the moment don't intend to fix them in the near future. The solution is simple: remove TorrentHandle of the magnet after receiving the metadata and create it again. A similar method is used in the synchronous method SessionManager.fetchMagnet

title: Ability to save torrent file automatically; remove delete torrent file option
message:
Ability to save torrent file automatically; remove delete torrent file option

The option of deleting .torrent files after beginning downloading became ambiguous after changing URI decoding mechanism of open file in app (support for more apps from which you can open a torrent file, see b9729fc commit), because if the URI is content://, then content provider in most cases doesn't allow deleting file (e.g. Chrome Dev, Via, native Email app and etc). This restricts the use of this option only files thath sent to the app as file://  URI (e.g. built-in file manager, some fthird-party file managers, Firefox) and sometimes as content:// URI (if it's MediaStore content provider).
If you have any suggestions how to solve this ambiguity, you can open the issue or make a pull request. So far, this option has been removed and replaced with the option to save .torrent file after beginning downloading (see #95 issue).

title: Removed Tor
message:
Removed Tor

Because Tor support has been subject strongly criticized by many users (e.g issue #4), it was decided to remove this feature.

You can use Tor for download torrents, but now it's not part of LibreTorrent. To do this, you can use third-party tools.
